This paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for social network curation, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also touches on the potential ethical concerns and need for regulation in the design of such systems, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
